description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Medical and Surgical Staff Nurse Vacancies (including for Student Nurses) in Warrington and Halton Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your Time, Your Career, Your WHH&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;BE PART OF THE CHANGES YOU WANT TO SEE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Warrington &amp; Halton Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust has a vision to provide high quality, safe and effective healthcare to the people of Warrington, Halton and their surrounding areas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There has never been a better time to join Warrington &amp; Halton Hospitals – we’re a well-established Trust with a great history, constantly striving to improve. A forward thinking recruitment philosophy creates fantastic opportunities for all our employees, whom we refer to as #TeamWHH, it is our aim to be the employer of choice within the region!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Registered Nurses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We at Warrington &amp; Halton Hospitals are looking for Staff Nurses to join our fabulous team. Whether you have recently finished your training or have a wealth of experience, we would like you to apply for a position with us, as long as you are a conscientious, adaptable and committed nurse who is passionate about their work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have full and part time permanent posts in the following areas:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Medicine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialist Medicine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respiratory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cardiology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Surgery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gastrenterology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As you can see, there is a wide variety of disciplines that you can choose to specialise in, which means you will have complete control over your career here at WHH.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are committed to making a difference, and want to work flexibly in a busy, vibrant environment, then this will be the opportunity for you. If you want to make a difference on a daily basis and go home feeling like you made the right choice about where to work, please apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Candidate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You, as the candidate, should:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have extensive knowledge of clinical practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have a positive, can-do attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have excellent communication and people skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;be able to thrive as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Benefits&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are some benefits of working with us that you won’t find anywhere else:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer &lt;strong&gt;flexible working hours&lt;/strong&gt;, regardless of whether you’re looking for full-time or part-time work. We even offer &lt;strong&gt;Night Only Contracts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll get the best experience with us because we have individual offers &lt;strong&gt;tailored to suit your needs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You get to choose&lt;/strong&gt; your specialty – revitalise your career and learn something new at the same time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Student Nurses&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated, conscientious and dynamic nurses who are awaiting their NMC registration. Whether you’re newly graduated or are expecting to finish your degree in the next 24 months, we would love for you to apply for a position with one of our fabulous teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role as a nurse will vary depending on which of our Clinical Business Units (CBUs) you join:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Urgent and Emergency Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrated Medicine and Community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surgical Specialties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Digestive Diseases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As you can see, there is a wide variety of disciplines that you can choose to specialise in, which means you will have complete control over your training experience with us. And if you start on a particular department and decide that it’s not for you, we will make it possible for you to switch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of your program, we can offer development and training, mentorship and a buddy that provides support with frequent meetings with the lead nurses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You, as the candidate, should:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have a sound knowledge of clinical procedures and protocol&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have excellent communication and people skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have a team-oriented mentality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have a true desire to learn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Benefits&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are some benefits of working with us that you won’t find anywhere else:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We’re willing to pay a &lt;strong&gt;Band 4 salary from the get-go&lt;/strong&gt; while you wait for your NMC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ll get the best training experience with us because we have individual offers &lt;strong&gt;tailored to suit your needs – &lt;/strong&gt;we’re fully flexible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A structured &lt;strong&gt;Preceptorship Program&lt;/strong&gt; comprising of; a bespoke induction, designated clinical skills educator, with protected rostered study leave and appropriate supernumerary status.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
